snippet.textDisplay:
Coke Studio is listened to by millions around the world. And so we need to put the quality work out there. If something's not upto par, we, as listeners and as music enthusiasts, should point it out.
For this version of Sayonee. To be honest, with all respect for Rahat Fateh Ali Khan and his hard work, this song didn't suit his voice (No doubt he is talented but that talent needs to be put to good use). This is made to be sung by someone with a manly, powerful (not Rahat's) voice. Plus he added all those unnecessary riffs and runs that literally made a mess of the entire song and made it sound like a song from a romantic Bollywood movie (at 2:11, 2:32).
Umair Jaswal could've sung this. Had Ali Noor been given more verses to sing, he would've sang it better than Rahat at least (at 7:15).

snippet.textDisplay: I read the comment the first.  Everyone was bashing the song.  I knew why we used to grew up listening this song in Ali Azmat voice and comparing it with Rahat Ji and Ali Noor was unfair.  They gave tribute to this song and Rahat Ji voice is no compare with Ali Azmat in every respect.  Rahat ji is the great singer and Ali Noor is well Reputed on another level.  But Ali Azmat gave this song the meaning that no one will replace it ever.  So it is unfair to curse these two good singers because of this song.  Although I did not like the first part but the last part after awesome guitar skill by Salman.  He gave this song true lift and music is better than the original no doubt  it's fast uplifting.  Second part singing is also really good.  Kiddos to this effort.
